newsitem.title: USA: FCOJ futures end slightly up in light trade.
newsitem.headline: FCOJ futures end slightly up in light trade.

text.p: Frozen concentrated orange juice futures closed barely firmer as the market maintainted a lathargic tone amid a dearth of news.

The most-active July contract closed up 0.10 cent at 74.85 cents per lb, having ranged from 75.00 to 74.60 cents. May closed 0.40 higher at 74.40, while the rest of the board ended 0.05 to 0.20 weaker.
Volume was estimated at 1,000 lots compared with Wednesday's official 1,023 lots.
Support in July remained at 72.00 cents and resistance at 78.00 cents.
There have been two delivery notices issued to date.
Players remain cautious ahead of Monday's U.S. Department of Agriculture estimate of the Florida crop. Analysts do not expect a change from the last estimate of 221.2 million 90-lb boxes, however.
Yields are seen steady at 1.57 gallons per box.
Brazil will release the first estimate of its 1997/98 crop, on May 20.
